portrait of a beauty ( hangul : 미인도 ; rr : miindo ) is a 2008 south korean film directed by jeon yun-su .   adapted from the bestselling novel painter of the wind ( hangul : 바람의 화원 ; rr : barame hwawon ) by lee jung-myung , the film portrays joseon-era painter shin yun-bok ( better known by his pen name , hyewon ) as being a woman disguised as a man .   portrait of a beauty opened in south korean theaters on 13 november 2008 .   it was the 8th most attended domestic film of 2008 with 2,364,482 tickets sold .